document.title: 2023 Indiana Academic Standards: Kindergarten - Grade 5 Physical Education

99E02A00193E4CAEB3B3642F9186BD22.description:
Describes the positive social interactions that come when engaged with
others in physical activity.

ACD71ACB5849434BBC763F1670E98349.description: Reflects on the reasons for enjoying selected physical activities.

35C331642E1C43A589AAFDEE5CC53673.description: Discusses the challenge that comes from learning a new physical activity.

E1AA2A3CBF3C4910A86434B620AA7F26.description: Discusses the relationship between physical activity and good health.

72C6BBC6633F400E9F28959107A978D4.description: Valuing Health, Enjoyment, Challenge, Self Expression, and Social Interaction

1047B5C961154FC29761DDF2D5393C33.description:
The physically literate individual recognizes the value of physical activity for health,
enjoyment, challenge, self expression and/or social interaction.

EA00BEE7A3494E2AA3C3AB21053B35F3.description:
Works safely with peers, independently, and with/without equipment in
physical activity settings.

7A5AC511EF494763A79EF96660E9F32C.description: Recognizes the role of rules and etiquette in physical activity with peers.

3D15DF6D30E249548EB95E33A7482D4C.description: Praises others for their success in movement performance.

23127F017FE343C985A8DEEB3A5AD545.description: Accepts and implements specific corrective feedback from the teacher.

CCD289FCCA2D4563A3360F293441E298.description: Works independently for extended periods of time.

3C5CA09A35294DD69797D2744FD69EBA.description: Exhibits responsible behavior in both independent and group situations

01240BC753744205A2B43557CDACA129.description:
The physically literate individual exhibits responsible personal and social behavior
that respects self and others.

AC9B86733B8B4CE4AF5338BABE2D0C33.description: Identifies foods that are beneficial for before and after physical activity.

BB7E9CBD1ADD48E68B4DB7FBE1BEA91D.description: Describes connections between muscular and skeletal systems.

07A46C67479449FD86643878985266DE.description: Demonstrates, with teacher direction, the health-related fitness components.

B1BCC32B4A1C4DA6ADEB899E57337D9E.description:
Recognizes the importance of warmup and cool-down relative to vigorous
physical activity.

C43FA470B47247E786F5BF985F41F157.description:
Describes the concept of fitness and provides examples of physical activity to
enhance fitness.

C72EF2CF9796472087B6CDD34504DAF5.description:
Actively engages in the activities of physical education class with minimal
teacher prompting.

4FD38C76CC144F70A4BF0C600BD97910.description: Identifies physical activity benefits as a way to become healthier.

2DEFA4977EF74A4F9CFD92E010C051DE.description:
Documents participation in physical activities outside physical education
class.

24D0DEB03C064E109E7383ED516BD6D6.description:
The physically literate individual demonstrates the knowledge and skills to achieve
and maintain a health-enhancing level of physical activity and fitness.

11A7A1200E24481493ED2ED54D6D5D35.description: Applies simple strategies and tactics in chasing and fleeing activities.

26F926FD311840019067CA06CAA09FB4.description:
Combines movement concepts (direction, levels, force, time) with skills as
directed by the teacher.

99A2045A879141DEB876D379E7FAE301.description: Recognizes locomotor skills specific to a wide variety of physical activities

5A29780FBA5846D483EAA766409DBE57.description: Recognizes the concept of open spaces in a movement context.

8E0891B3DF604E61A0C5926D2E8E1B34.description:
The physically literate individual applies knowledge of concepts, principles,
strategies and tactics related to movement and performance.

448627C9D0034D438A1435FD146065BE.description:
Performs intermediate jump rope skills (such as a variety of tricks, running in and
out of long rope) for both long and short ropes.

0144A94F7BB14980A7CAA0A587241692.description:
Strikes a ball with a long-handled implement (such as a hockey stick, bat, golf
club), sending it forward, while using proper grip for the implement. Note: Use a batting tee
or ball tossed by the teacher for batting.

9FD506917E9542A6B0B18194CB116B0D.description:
Strikes an object with a short- handled implement, sending it forward over a low
net or to a wall.

E911B9DCDEC34B889BD7FC715ED23384.description:
Demonstrates emerging pattern while striking an object underhand or sidearm,
sending it upward and forward.

C2AC58E06E8A47FE85D4462659DF43A8.description: Performs mature pattern while receiving with the foot when stationary.

F1AD9BBE4DDE4DA1A2FD8871656C3085.description:
Dribbles with the feet in general space at slow to moderate jogging speed with
control of ball and body.

58D31E36514349058C2F218E6BCABAE2.description: Uses a running approach and kicks a stationary ball for accuracy.

FF04F4A403844462A639501E7944C8C8.description:
Demonstrates a mature pattern and intentionally performs a kick along the ground
and a kick in the air, demonstrating four of the five critical elements of a mature pattern for
each.

C4D70DEDB4E5410B9934B51AD47C73D5.description:
Passes & receives a ball with the inside of the foot to a stationary partner, “giving”
on reception before returning the pass.

7151D45CFCF345B08127C2832B9D4AB9.description:
Dribbles and travels in general space at slow to moderate jogging speed, with
control of ball and body.

783EC3436AE64D97A7DA435E187CDDFA.description:
Catches a gently tossed hand-size ball from a partner, demonstrating a mature
pattern in a non-dynamic environment.

6811EBB1A1D441F687060BF7DA2A45B4.description: Developmentally appropriate/emerging outcomes first appear in grade four.

8124BD8979F9428B8B82A3512AD1B4F7.description: Performs mature pattern in an overhand throw.

F5A88399027148AC8625A6E46E570FBE.description: Throws underhand to a partner or target with reasonable accuracy.

F12D15B446E1434AB69F17CBEA7CBF72.description:
Balances on different bases of support, demonstrating muscular tension and
extensions of free body parts, and shows ability to transfer weight from feet to hand for
momentary weight support.

00ABA9D797A54753ACC057C7AEB3612D.description: Applies mature patterns in nonlocomotor skills in a variety of activities.

E1F3BFD9956547F8B831250D3FF7444B.description:
Performs teacher selected and developmentally appropriate dance steps and
movement patterns.

553E5852B76C4B61B9C5FA3357B15217.description: Jumps and lands in the horizontal and vertical planes using an emerging pattern.

87BD68A61A5E487D863893A1EC2A380B.description: Locomotor (Jumping and landing in a horizontal and vertical plane)

8A2DDB6A34E148319390CC292FD9A48C.description: Applies mature patterns in locomotor skills in a variety of activities.

F8A3ABFD5CCE4E4494261334178EA716.description: Performs mature patterns in locomotor skills in isolation (leap).

67FB6FB4F3FD4CDEAFAB684CEC45FF29.description: Locomotor (Hopping, galloping, running, sliding, skipping, leaping, walking, running)

473EE739EDFB4A87A5C6F51CA272FDF4.description:
The physically literate individual will demonstrate competency in a variety of motor
skills and movement patterns.
